  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the fries are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679316308941-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679316308941-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679316308941-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679316308941-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679316308941-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 80ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [160ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken thighs </strong>to the <strong>marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then set aside until later</p><p>Tip: This will help to tenderise your chicken!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679316312695-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679316312695-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679316312695-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679316312695-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679316312695-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> finely into discs</p><p>Add the <strong>cucumber discs</strong> and the<strong> remaining cider vinegar</strong> to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and set aside – these are your<strong> quick-pickled cucumbers</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1679316317282-x200.jpg",
